gomodel:SYNGO_2759  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.2: \"Neurexin Clusters GABA and NMDA Glutamate Receptors\"\nFig.3: \"Neurexin Clusters Neuroligins but Not Dystroglycan\"\nFig.4: \"Purified Neurexin Coclusters Neuroligins with Postsynaptic Proteins\"\nFig.5: \"Neuroligin Aggregation Alone Is Synaptogenic\"\n- \"Transfection of neurons with low levels of YFP-neuroligin followed by application of beads bearing anti-YFP antibodies resulted in local clustering of the YFP-neuroligin on the surface of transfected dendrites. Such direct aggregation of YFP-neuroligin-1 resulted in coaggregation of PSD-95 but not gephyrin (Figure 5A).\". Experimental description: - \"Hippocampal neuron cultures were prepared from E18 rat embryos...\"\n- Species of overexpressed NLGN2; neuroligin 2 is not stated in the paper. Authors were contacted for information (2/3/2018, peter.scheiffele@unibas.ch). Answer was:\n\n\"Hi Pim,\nAll cDNAs were originally cloned from mouse (Scheiffele et al., Cell, 2000)\nBest,\nPeter\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-03" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2759" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

